14/07/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four soldiers died Monday (July 13th) in what appears to have been an accidental ammunition explosion in the southeastern province of Hakkari. 
According to media reports Tuesday, it happened at a military post near the border with Iraq.
In other news, one police officer was killed and another person was injured by gunmen in the southeastern city of Diyarbakir late Sunday, media reported Monday. 
The attackers opened fire in front of the offices of the Nokta company in the city's Baglar district. 
(NTV, CNNTurk, Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Reuters, AP, AFP - 14/07/09; Dogan news agency, Hurriyet - 13/07/09)
